{
  "texts": [
    "The hyperparameter α controls the update speed of the teacher network's parameters.",
    "After obtaining the pseudo-labels, we perform category-wise mixing of samples from the source and target domains:x mix = x S ⊙ M + x T ⊙ (1 -M) y mix = y S ⊙ M + ȳT ⊙ (1 -M)(16)where (x S, y S) is the data sample from the source domain, and M is generated by randomly selecting half of the categories based on the labels of the source domain y S. The Optimization objective for the DA task if defined by:arg min θ,ϵ,ξ (x,y)∈D∪Dmix L seg (G θ,ξ,ϵ (x), y) + λ uda L seg (G θ,ξ,ϵ (x mix), y mix).",
    "(17) Hyper-Parameter ConfigurationAs shown in Table 7, we provide an overview of training hyperparameters.",
    "Specifically, for DA and DG tasks, we train for 20k iterations with a batch size of 4; for SS tasks, we train for 40k iterations with a batch size of 8.",
    "Notably, for the iSAID SS task, we train for 80k iterations with a batch size of 8."
  ]
}